title: Google\Cloud\AppEngine\V1\Deployment
name: Deployment
description:
Code and application artifacts used to deploy a version to App Engine.

Generated from protobuf message google.appengine.v1.Deployment

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.files
params.description: Manifest of the files stored in Google Cloud Storage that are included as part of this version. All files must be readable using the credentials supplied with this call.

params.name: data.container
params.description: The Docker image for the container that runs the version. Only applicable for instances running in the App Engine flexible environment.

params.name: data.zip
params.description: The zip file for this deployment, if this is a zip deployment.

params.name: data.cloud_build_options
params.description: Options for any Google Cloud Build builds created as a part of this deployment. These options will only be used if a new build is created, such as when deploying to the App Engine flexible environment using files or zip.
